description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join us at Wellington Community Hospital and be involved in pioneering the future of patient care, close to home, family, friends and local community support.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a 10 bedded rehabilitation unit, nurses and therapists work together in supporting patients regain their independence during their hospital stay, with the aim of returning the patient home. We deliver personalised, high quality, compassionate care in line with an agreed care plan. We have a 2 full time vacancies for enthusiastic, dynamic and motivated Health Care Assistants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have development opportunities for staff and are committed to enabling members of the Nursing team to reach their full potential through experience and additional training, development and education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will support patients to enable independence for all of our patients ensuring that patients are treated with dignity and respect. You will be able to promote a safe environment within the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work flexibly on an internal rotation, which will include working days and nights over 7 days. In return you will receive enhanced payments for weekend working, a generous holiday entitlement and pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Lampey&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07864 742565&lt;/p&gt;
